snippet: The former president of Honduras and a former FIFA vice president pleaded not guilty in federal court to charges stemming from the investigation of bribes and kickbacks.
abstract: Former FIFA vice president Juan Angel Napout and former Honduran Pres Rafael Callejas plead not guilty to charges connected to FIFA corruption scandal; other soccer news noted.
lead_paragraph: The former president of Honduras and a former FIFA vice president pleaded not guilty in federal court to charges stemming from the investigation of bribes and kickbacks.

headline.main: Not Guilty Plea Entered in FIFA Case
